OL,3,CTrump mocks Starmer as weak as UK
OL,4,Cleads push to reopen Strait of Hormuz
OL,6,FIn the face of ongoing military
OL,7,Fstrikes by the US and Israel, Iran has
OL,8,Ftightened its grip on the maritime
OL,9,Fpinchpoint of the Strait of Hormuz,
OL,10,Fsending global oil and gas prices
OL,11,Fskyrocketing.
OL,13,FForeign Secretary Yvette Cooper has
OL,14,Fsignalled Iran could face further
OL,15,Fsanctions if the vital waterway
OL,16,Fremains closed after holding talks
OL,17,Fwith more than 40 nations from across
OL,18,Fthe world.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31607
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1775289887
OL,3,CTrump mocks Starmer as weak as UK
OL,4,Cleads push to reopen Strait of Hormuz
OL,6,FShe said collective action to increase
OL,7,Fpressure on Tehran was being discussed
OL,8,Fas she accused the country of trying
OL,9,Fto "hold the global economy hostage"
OL,10,Fwith its stranglehold on the key trade
OL,11,Froute.
OL,13,FIn the face of criticism by Mr Trump,
OL,14,FMs Cooper said that "our job is to
OL,15,Ftake decisions in the UK national
OL,16,Finterest".
OL,26,@qD@DOUqD@dO]vD@UOUxD@IO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/12
